data.name: label8.ToolTip
data.value:
Whether the value changes every beat (step = TRUE)(utilizing default on empty beats), or interoplates between set data points (step = FALSE)
Only useful for Trait types of kTraitFloat and kTraitColor

data.name: btnTrackPlayback.ToolTip
data.value:
***CURRENTLY BUGGY. SKIPS BEATS SOMETIMES*** Click to playback the entire leaf. Plays these objects in time: -Thumps -Turns -Bars and Rings -Jumps -Millipedes -Samples
Playback speed is dependant on the Master BPM.

data.name: label46.ToolTip
data.value: Interpolation type between beat values. Higher interpolation = smoother transitions/curves, but higher intensity calculation. Can decrease FPS. THIS AFFECTS IN-GAME ONLY. NOT THIS EDITOR'S INTERPOLATION CALC.

data.name: label20.ToolTip
data.value:
Editing works the same way as the leaf editor. You can use float (decimals) between 0 and 1 to change a sample/loop track volume throughout the lvl. 0 = off
This is useful to make certain loop tracks quieter so they don't drown out other sounds at specific times.
